A minimalistic architectural illustration featuring a pristine white hexagonal prism floating in a soft gradient space, with six distinct colored cables or conduits connecting to each face of the hexagon like docking ports. Each cable transforms into a different geometric shape at its outer end - a sphere, cube, pyramid, cylinder, cone, and torus - representing diverse adapters. The hexagon's core glows with a warm amber light, suggesting protected inner logic. The composition uses clean lines, generous negative space, and a muted palette of slate blue, coral, sage green, and cream. Subtle grid lines in the background evoke technical precision without being overwhelming. The perspective is slightly isometric, giving depth while maintaining the clean, diagrammatic quality of thoughtful software design.
